Sentencas: Mechanical properties of nickel and yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) anodes of solid oxide fuel cells undergo changes not only because of extrinsic conditions but also because of Ni, YSZ and pore proportions.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: In this study, elastic modulus and fracture behavior of Ni(NiO)-YSZ composites are investigated with changing Ni and pore volume fractions as the main parameters.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: NiO-YSZ composite stiffness at 800 degrees C monotonically increases with increasing NiO.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: However, the reduced form of Ni-YSZ shows drastic changes in elastic modulus and strength around 30 vol% Ni where the deformation behavior and fracture made transition from brittle-like to ductile.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: Both stiffness and strength show linear decreases with porosity, of which the degree of deterioration at 800 degrees C was duller than at room temperature.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: The influences of Ni content and porosity on elasticity are quantified using multiple-linear regression analysis.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: Pore volume fraction shows large negative effects on elasticity at room temperature in air.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: However, at 800 degrees C, Ni volume shows larger negative effects than pore volume under reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: Influences of Ni content and porosity on mechanical properties of Ni-YSZ composites under solid oxide fuel cell operating conditions
